<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Anticipates No Change on Ties With Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Russia will continue giving
priority to the development of its relations with Germany, Russian
Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov told visiting German Chancellor
Gerhard Schroeder on Monday.
</P>
<P>
During their 40-minute meeting, Primakov confirmed that
Russian-German relations would be marked by continuity and were
not dependent on which government was in power.
</P>
<P>
"We understand the importance of Germany in Europe and the
world and closely analyze Germany's path to present prosperity
after the Second World War. We would like to study your experience
closer," said Primakov.
</P>
<P>
Schroeder, in turn, expressed his agreement with the host,
saying, "The quality of German-Russian relations is high and
the new government of Germany is interested in continuity.
</P>
<P>
"But new additional concerns may appear too," he added.
</P>
<P>
Schroeder arrived here on Monday for a two-day official visit.
He is expected to meet with Russian President Boris Yeltsin on
Tuesday, as well as the chairmen of both chambers of parliament,
Gennady Seleznyov and Yegor Stroyev. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
