<HEADLINE> France Not to Back Action to Topple Saddam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 16 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine said on Monday that France would refuse to support any
action to topple Iraqi President Saddam Hussein.
</P>
<P>
"France does not support the tradition of doing what the United
States, in the name of the law which it gives itself, estimates
what it is possible to say and do," said Vedrine in an interview
with the Europe One television channel.
</P>
<P>
He said that it was not the tradition of French diplomacy to
interfere in the internal affairs of another nation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he pointed out that the level of patience of the
international community towards Iraq -- including those
sympathetic to the suffering of the Iraqi people -- diminished
each time Iraq stopped cooperation with the U.N. inspectors.
</P>
</TEXT>
