<HEADLINE> Iran Reiterates Support for Lebanese Resistance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami on Monday reiterated Tehran's support for the Lebanese
resistance against Israel's aggression.
</P>
<P>
Khatami made the remark in a meeting with visiting Lebanese
Prime Minister Rafik Hariri, who arrived here Monday morning, the
official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Israel carved out a self-declared security zone in south
Lebanon in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from
cross-border attacks by Lebanese guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance has been fighting to dislodge
Israeli occupying forces and its proxy South Lebanon Army out of
the country.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the Middle East peace process, Khatami said Iran
believes that the real peace can only be formed in the region when
the rights and dignity of the Palestinians are fully observed.
</P>
<P>
Khatami also expressed the hope that relations between Iran and
Lebanon will further broaden on the basis of good will and
determination of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Iran and Lebanon can play a significant role in influencing
regional and global issues, he said.
</P>
<P>
Terming detente policy as the most pivotal principle of Iran's
foreign diplomacy, the Iranian president said "we never welcome
any move that might spark a crisis."
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Hariri briefed Khatami on the post-civil
war (1975-1990) reconstruction projects under way in Lebanon.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
