<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1430 GMT, November 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT -- One Israeli soldier was killed and five others
wounded in south Lebanon Monday by a roadside bomb, the Orient
radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The bomb was detonated by anti-Israeli Lebanese guerrillas
when an armored Israeli patrol passed by on a road in the Markab
area, in the central sector of the Israeli occupied south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
In Beirut, the Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God,
claimed responsibility for the attack, saying one of its units
planted a bomb and killed and wounded all soldiers of an Israeli
patrol. (Lebanon-Israeli Killed)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said here Monday
morning that the successful exchange of visits between the leaders
of China and the United States will help bring the
Sino-U.S. relationship to a new high.
</P>
<P>
"When President Clinton visited China in June, we decided to
make concerted efforts to establish a constructive strategic
partnership between China and the United States and set the goals
for the development of the Sino-U.S. relations in the new
century," said Jiang in a meeting with U.S. Vice President Al
Gore. (APEC-China-US-Relations)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- The U.N. relief workers, who were evacuated to
Amman, Jordan last week amid the Iraq-U.N. standoff over arms
inspections, will return to Iraq on Monday afternoon to resume
their mandate.
</P>
<P>
Eric Falt, spokesman for the U.N. Office of Humanitarian
Coordinator in Iraq (UNOHCI), told reporters Monday that 30
U.N. humanitarian staff will arrive by plane at Habbaniya airport,
80 kilometers west of Baghdad at 1:30 p.m. local time.
</P>
<P>
Falt said that 121 others are arriving via Amman-Baghdad
highway, the major land route to and from Iraq. (Iraq-UN
Workers-Return)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG -- The Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) Monday
urged South Africa to press for the withdrawal of Ugandan and
Rwandan forces from the DRC.
</P>
<P>
Once troops from the two countries had retreated, an African
peacekeeping force should be deployed along the DRC borders during
its transition to democracy, visiting DRC Foreign Minister
Jean-Charles Okotololakombe told reporters in Pretoria, capital of
South Africa, after meeting with his South African counterpart
Alfred Nzo.
</P>
<P>
Okotololakombe called on South African President Nelson
Mandela, chairman of the Southern African Development Community,
"to play his true role and ask these countries to leave our
country," press reports here said. (DRC-Army Withdraw)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said here Monday
afternoon that the Chinese government has adopted a responsible
attitude toward the financial crisis and maintained the value of
Chinese currency, Renminbi (RMB), which in turn has made positive
contributions to easing up the crisis.
</P>
<P>
"China will deepen its reforms and accelerate the process of
opening up to the outside world, so as to strive to meet the
target growth rate of this year's GDP (gross domestic product),"
Jiang said while meeting with Australian Prime Minister John
Howard here.
</P>
<P>
Howard expressed his appreciation of China maintaining the
value of the RMB even under the difficult domestic circumstances
brought about by the severe floods. He also praised China's
promise of further opening up to the outside
world. (APEC-Jiang-Australian)
</P>
<P>
