</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- At least 125 buildings were damaged and looted
during the riots that erupted Saturday following clashes between
student demonstrators and security forces, Antara News Agency
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Provisional data obtained by Antara indicated that the figure
includes two wet markets, two supermarkets, 84 shops, eight hotels
 and restaurants, six government offices, four private offices, 15
 banks and one workshop.
</P>
<P>
One police station was also damaged and one gasoline station
was set on fire. Houses and places of worship were however
spared. (Indonesia-Riots) 
