<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WIPO Holds First Afro-Arab Symposium on Copyright </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, November 16 (Xinhua) -- The World Intellectual Property
Organization (WIPO) is holding its first Afro-Arab Symposium on
Copyright and Related Rights from November 16 to 18 in Tunis.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from all the Arab countries and some 15
French-speaking and English-speaking countries of Africa will
attend the three-day symposium, said WIPO in a press release here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The aim of this symposium is to provide the African and Arab
states with the opportunity of examining and discussing the
present norms for the protection of authors' rights and
neighboring rights and the application of those measures within
the context of the Agreement on Trade-Related Aspects of
Intellectual Property Rights (TRIPS).
</P>
<P>
The meeting will also discuss the policy and activities
proposed by those states in order to implement the necessary
administrative and legislative measures for the successful
operation of the TRIPS agreement.
</P>
<P>
The symposium will offer an opportunity for addressing the
economic significance of electronic commerce and its intellectual
property aspects in relation to the trading activities pursued
through the processing and transmission of digital data. 
</P>
</TEXT>
