<HEADLINE> Pakistan releases 39 More Indian Fishermen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan on Monday released
39 more Indian fishermen and five more boats, raising the number
of freed Indian fishermen to 190, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Indian fishermen were handed over to the Indian officials
in Karachi, who are likely to proceed to India this week.
</P>
<P>
A total of 151 Indian fishermen and 26 boats were released
last Thursday.
