announcement by Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif during the foreign
secretary-level talks between Pakistan and India held in Islamabad
last month.
</P>
<P>
India has also agreed to release Pakistani fishermen and their
boats. Indian officials said in New Delhi that Pakistani fishermen
will be freed after the arrival of a Pakistani delegation to
India.
</P>
<P>
India is reported to have held 148 Pakistani fishermen and
their 15 boats. 
