<HEADLINE> Iran, Oman Sign Agreement on Military Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Defense Minister Ali
Shamkhani and his Omani counterpart Badr bin Saud bin Hareb
al-Busaidi signed an agreement here Monday on military and
logistical cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, military experts of the two countries will
be allowed to take part in military exercises of the other side,
the official Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Al-Busaidi, who arrived here Saturday, said there is no
obstacle to the implementation of the agreement and a joint
military friendship committee of the two countries will follow up
the agreement.
</P>
<P>
He said an Omani delegation of military experts will visit Iran
to prepare for the implementation of the accord.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that the Oman-Iran military agreement will
set a pattern for defense cooperation among the region.
</P>
<P>
Shamkhani, on his part, said the agreement will serve the
security and stability of the Gulf region.
</P>
<P>
Al-Busaidi wound up his three-day visit to Tehran Monday
afternoon and left here. 
</P>
