<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Seeks $242m for Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 16 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Social
Rehabilitation and Development Fund announces Monday that it
needs about 242 million U.S. Dollars to accomplish its
objectives.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, the fund hopes to
obtain the stated sum from creditors, donor states and agencies,
the Ethiopian government as well as the public at large.
</P>
<P>
The fund, which was established two years ago, has a five-year
program with objectives of establishing and consolidating basic
social service facilities and improving the living standard of
the Ethiopian rural people.
</P>
<P>
To date, the fund has carried out 866 projects that focus,
among others, on the construction of health and educational
institutions as well as potable water and irrigation schemes.
</P>
<P>
The fund says it has managed to collect 44.8 million Dollars
of the 197.87 million Dollars pledged to it so far. 
</P>
