<HEADLINE> France Promotes Idea of "Defense Agency" within EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 16 (Xinhua) -- France Monday again promoted the
idea of establishing a "defense agency" within the European Union
(EU) to better coordinate multinational military units that have
been functioning in Europe.
</P>
<P>
French Delegate Minister in charge of European affairs, Piere
Moscovici, said at a meeting of EU defense and foreign ministers
in Rome that such an agency would lead "political and strategic"
operations, have its own intelligence system, and better cordinate
multinational forces in Europe.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse (AFP) said that Moscovici was quoted by an
anonymous source of the Western European Union, but no further
information can be obtained from the French delegation attending
the meeting in Rome.
</P>
<P>
Moscovici also suggested that EU create a list of institutions
to be established for defense issues, and promoted the idea of
European defense in the charter of North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) which is undergoing revisions, and reform, if
need be, the multinational military units in Europe, according to
the same source.
</P>
<P>
The term "agency" was first used by French President Jacques
Chirac in August to propose a future body within the EU in charge
of defense.
</P>
<P>
French Defense Minister Alain Richard Monday also suggested
that EU create a permanent international peace envoy based on the
U.S. model for participating in negotiating the crises such as
those in Kosovo and Iraq.  
</P>
</TEXT>
