<HEADLINE> Romania: 2,500 Kgs of Drugs Confiscated in First </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, November 16 (Xinhua) -- More than 2,500 kgs of drugs
and narcotics were confiscated by the Customs' officers in the
first ten months of the year, the Customs' General Directorate
informed on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The drug quantities varied from three grams to 2,200 kgs. The
quantity of heroin confiscated by the Customs' officers was the
largest one, namely, 312.6 kgs. More than three quarters of the
quantity was confiscated from persons who left Romania.
</P>
<P>
The ways the drugs were hidden were various, from commonplace
ways - pockets, backpacks - to very clever ones - pillows, a
doll's head and a book's cover. The drugs traffickers were from
Nigeria, Turkey, Fyrom, Croatia, the Czech Republic, the Republic
of Moldova, Ireland and Romania.
</P>
<P>
Romania has become, since early 90's, an important transfer
point of drugs from the Central Asia to the Western Europa, due to
its geographical position. Statistics show that the drug smuggle
cases cracked by the authorities in the recent 9 years are of 40
times more than in the previous 20 years. 7,300 kgs of drugs were
captured in 1997. 
</P>
