<HEADLINE> Romania's Foreign Debt Stands at 8.339 Bln Dlrs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Romania's long- and
medium-term foreign debt topped 8.339 billion U.S. dollars at the
end of August, about 31 million down from the end of 1997,
according to the latest data released Monday by the Central Bank.
</P>
<P>
The public debt stood at about 4.5 billion U.S. dollars, or 54
percent of the total debt, the state-guaranteed public debt at
1.97 billion U.S. dollars and the private commercial debt at 1.8
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Romania owed in August to international financial lenders 3.273
billion U.S. dollars, out of which the highest debt, about 1.436
billion, goes to the International Bank for Reconstruction and
Development. The International Monetary Fund, the European Union
and the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development were
among the other important lenders.
</P>
<P>
The credits granted to Romania by private banks of Germany,
France, Great Britain and the United States totaled in August more
than 1.6 billion U.S. dollars. Romania's biggest creditors from
among foreign private banks are from Great Britain, with 410
million U.S. dollars and France, with 383 millions, followed by
banks from Germany, 224 millions and the United States, 201
millions. 
</P>
