<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-16 20:53 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Algeria to Launch Small Firms to Curtail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Algeria will launch some 8,000
small enterprises over the next year to create new job
opportunities, Minister of Labor, Social Security and Professional
Training Hacene Laskri announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The move is designed to absorb unemployment that affects almost
all communities due to the current economic transformations
nationwide, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
The 1999 Algerian budget allocates 6.5 billion Algerian dinars
(112 million U.S. dollars) to provide more than 170,000 new jobs,
out of which 86,000 are permanent ones, Laskri said before the
National People Assembly (Algerian Parliament).
</P>
<P>
The minister pointed out that all institutions and agencies
concerned with fighting unemployment should contribute to the
elimination of the unemployment phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
He urged the institutions including the National Authority for
Social Development, the National Fund for Insurance against
Unemployment and the National Authority for Youth Employment to
give a hand to those who are willing to initiate economic
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment rate in Algeria now stands at 28 percent. More
than 2 million people are unemployed, mostly youth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
