<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Foreign Minister
Abdus Samad Azad Tuesday hoped that the country's development
partners would continue to help implement its post-flood
rehabilitation programs.
</P>
<P>
"You have been our partners for progress for many, many years,"
Azad said at a brief meeting here with heads of diplomatic
missions and international agencies.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his thanks for their continued assistance,
particularly their generous response during the unprecedented
flood the country experienced recently.
</P>
