<HEADLINE> China Pushing Fine Ceramic Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 17 (Xinhua) -- China, the world's largest
exporter of ceramics, is making every effort to improve the quality
of its household ceramic products, according to Huo Dufang,
president of the China Ceramic Industry Association.
</P>
<P>
Huo told a press conference here today that low added-value
products make up the lion's share of China's ceramic exports, and
the unit price for Chinese products is much lower than the world
average.
</P>
<P>
A china art and design fair will be held in Shanghai in
December, with 200,000 pieces of china to be on display, which
is expected to raise china design and production technology to a
new level.
</P>
<P>
Huo says that China's ceramics industry will put more emphasis
on tableware, which accounts for the bulk of household china on
the world market and that bone china and other fine products will
be the focus of it.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that half of China's ceramics exports are
decorative items or souvenirs.
</P>
<P>
China exported 1.46 billion U.S. dollars worth of ceramic
products in 1997, accounting for 63.5 percent of the world's total
ceramics exports.  
</P>
