<HEADLINE> Chinese Capital's First Death Sentence For Dealing In Prostitution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Ma Yulan, a 41-year-old woman
who organized a prostitution ring, was sentenced to death by the
Intermediate People's Court of Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Ma has become the first woman to receive the death penalty in
Beijing for dealing in prostitution.
</P>
<P>
It was not reported whether Ma would exercise her right to file
an appeal to a higher court.
</P>
<P>
Organizing a prostitution ring carries new penalties under the
country's revised Criminal Law.
</P>
<P>
In addition to receiving the death penalty, Ma was deprived of
her political rights and forfeited her personal property.
</P>
<P>
Ma opened a restaurant and sauna business in Beijing's
Shijingshan District in June, 1996, and turned it into an
underground brothel business that employed local women.
</P>
<P>
Eight other people implicated in the same crime were given
1-and-a-half to 8 years in prison. 
</P>
