the Taliban before the murderers of Iranian diplomats and a
correspondent in Afghanistan are arrested and punished, a
remaining Iranian captive is freed and the Taliban leaders
officially apologize to Iran.
</P>
<P>
On August 8, the Taliban killed eight Iranian diplomats and an
IRNA reporter after its troops run over Mazar-e-Sharif in northern
Afghanistan. It also held more than scores of Iranian truck
drivers accused of sending arms to the opposition Northern
Alliance.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban returned the remains of the killed Iranian
diplomats and reporter and released 51 Iranian captives after
Tehran massed over 200,000 troops along the eastern border and
staged massive military exercises. 
