<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Calls for Closer Econtech Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin called here Tuesday for closer Economic and Technological
Cooperation(Econtech) within the framework of APEC (Asia-Pacific
Economic Cooperation).
</P>
<P>
The Chinese President made the call at a meeting of the APEC
Business Advisory Council (ABAC) held at the Palace of Golden
Horse Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Econtech and trade and investment liberalization, which are
mutually complimentary and reinforcing, are two main pillars of
the APEC, said Jiang, adding that a balanced development of the
two is an important condition for ensuring the healthy evolvement
of the APEC.
</P>
<P>
He further noted that Econtech is one of the important ways to
realize APEC's objective of bridging the gap of development among
its member economies and achieving common prosperity.
</P>
<P>
"it is also a fundamental guarantee for APEC to maintain its
dynamism," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"Facts have shown that without fruitful economic and
technological cooperation, it is very difficult for trade and
investment liberalization to make headway", the Chinese president
said.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, under the current circumstances, we should fully
recognize the importance and urgency of strengthening Econtech
cooperation within the APEC", he said.
</P>
<P>
In the past years, APEC members have been actively engaged in
cooperative initiatives in the field of Econtech, which have
yielded many positive results, President Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"Thanks to the concerted efforts by the APEC members and the
business community, we have completed the work of drafting the
Kuala Lumpur Action Program on Skills Development and the APEC
Agenda for Science and Technology Industry Cooperation into the
21st Century," Jiang said, while predicting the Action Program and
the Agenda as blueprints for future APEC cooperation in this field.
</P>
<P>
"It is our hope that the parties concerned will work together
to explore an effective and mutually beneficial way of
cooperation, so that enterprises can better involve themselves in
the APEC Econtech cooperation," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The ABAC was established in 1995 with the aim to facilitate
involvement of business sector in the APEC cooperation. It has 54
members and reports to the annual APEC leaders' informal meeting.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's meeting was attended by 20 leaders of APEC member
economies and representatives from the business community of the
region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
