<HEADLINE> Macao, HK Police Seize 12 kg of Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Macao police succeeded in
cooperating with police in Hong Kong in seizing 12 kilograms of
heroin at the Chek Lap Kok Airport of Hong Kong on November 7.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued Tuesday by the Judicial Police
Department of Macao said the heroin is worth 11 million patacas
(1.375 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Concealed in three packages for express delivery, the drug was
smuggled into Hong Kong from Bangkok. The packages were claimed to
be paper mailed to Macao.
</P>
<P>
Police in Macao and Hong Kong tried to deliver the packages
according to the address on them, only to find that the address to
Macao was false.
</P>
<P>
Police in Macao, Hong Kong and Thailand have made concerted
efforts to investigate the drug-smuggling case. Up to now, nine
suspects have been inquired. 
</P>
