<HEADLINE> Mongolian Exports Plummet in First Ten Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian exports dropped
sharply with a trade deficit of 128 million U.S. dollars in the
first ten months this year, said the Mongolian National Statistics
Agency on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Foreign trade in the first ten months totaled 638.6 million
dollars with a downturn of 5.7 percent from last year. Export
volume plunged 23.6 percent to 255.1 million dollars and import
volume was up 11.7 percent to 383.5 million dollars, said the
agency.
</P>
<P>
The main reason for the retreat is that the international
prices of brass, gold and cashmere, which serve as Mongolia's
pillar export products, have fallen greatly.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia conducts trade with more than 70 other countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
