<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asian Conference on Remote Sensing Opens in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The 19th Asian Conference on
Remote Sensing (ACRS) opened here Monday to discuss the latest
developments in remote sensing and the geographic information
system in the region.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is being organized by the Asian Association on
Remote Sensing, National Mapping and Resource Information
Authority (NAMRIA), and the Department of Science and Technology
(DOST).
</P>
<P>
Remote sensing refers to the collection of data using sensing
devices or sensors which are not in direct contact with the object
being observed.
</P>
<P>
It also involves the evaluation of the collected data and
presentation of the results of such evaluation in the form of maps
and statistics.
</P>
<P>
NAMRIA Administrator Liberato Manuel said the holding of the
conference is significant because "it provides a venue for
discussing the latest developments in remote sensing and the
geographic information system (GIS), with hopes of addressing the
serious environmental problems being experienced by countries in
Asia."
</P>
<P>
Manuel said that application of state-of-the-art technology
such as remote sensing and GIS "contributes to more efficient and
faster monitoring, assessment and inventory of the environment
and natural resources."
</P>
<P>
He said that the objective of the five-day meeting is to
resolve problems in remote sensing and GIS, and promote
applications of remote sensing and space technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
