<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Hero Striker Papin Sets to Retire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 35-year-old scoring hero made 326 goals in 584 matches for
eight clubs and the French national team.
</P>
<P>
In 54 matches for France, including 11 as captain, Papin
scored 30 goals, setting a record bettered only by Michel
Platini, and played in the 1986 World Cup finals and 1992
European Championships.
</P>
<P>
Papin shot to fame in 1986 after signing for Marseille, where
he scored 181 goals in 279 games, won four championship medals
and was top French goalscorer for five seasons.
</P>
<P>
After transferring to AC Milan in 1992, Papin won a European
Cup medal in 1994, though he didn't play in the final against his
former club Marseille.
</P>
<P>
Papin also played for Bayern Munich, helping the Germany club
win the UEFA Cup in 1996, before moving back to France and
joining the second division club Guingamp in pre-season.
</P>
<P>
Other clubs Papin played for included Vichy, Valenciennes,
Bruges and Bordeaux. 
</P>
</TEXT>
