<HEADLINE> Establishment in Singapore Selected as Winner of the </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The Southeast Asia Ministers
of Education Organization --Regional Language Center (SEAMEO-RELC)
in Singapore has emerged as the winner of the ASEAN Award in the
organizational category this year, Singapore Ministry of Foreign
Affairs announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The award will be presented to the winners by the Leaders at
the ASEAN Summit due to be held in Hanoi from December 15 to 16,
1998.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN Award was established by the ASEAN Heads of
Government at the 5th Summit in December 1995 in a bid to raise
the public profile of ASEAN activities. The Award, to be presented
triennially at the ASEAN Summits, recognizes the outstanding
contributions by individuals and organizations to promote and
develop regional cooperation in ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
According to the ministry, this year's winners were selected by
an ASEAN Panel of Judges, which comprised the chairmen of the
various countries' National ASEAN Award Search Committee as the
Panel met in Jakarta from October 27 t0 28, 1998. The Panel's
decision was subsequently endorsed by the ASEAN Standing Committee
Meeting.
</P>
<P>
The RELC has trained over 12,000 English language teachers
since 1968, most of them from ASEAN countries.
</P>
<P>
Over the last seven years, more than 1,200 ASEAN nationals,
including students and senior civil servants, have also learnt
English at the RELC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
