<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Meeting on Aid to Malawi to Convene Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The Consultative Group (CG)
meeting on aid to Malawi will be held next month in Malawian
capital Lilongwe instead of the traditional venue of Paris,
Zambian newspaper Financial Mail reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will have a wider involvement of the government
ministries and stakeholders, said the paper.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent statement from the World Bank country
director for Angola, Malawi and Zimbabwe, Barbara Kafka, this
year's meeting is expected to have a special session on poverty
to include discussions on government's poverty alleviation, AIDS,
population and safety net strategies.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the meeting, the World Bank is going to hold a
briefing on the CG while donors participating in the meeting will
have a field trip to a number of different project sites in
Malawi.
</P>
<P>
A CG meeting is usually a gathering of developing countrys'
donors for the purpose of reviewing recent developments and
challenges ahead.
</P>
<P>
The donors usually clarify at the meeting the level and nature
of their financial commitments for the coming year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
