<HEADLINE> 7 Killed, 39 Injured in India-Held Kashmir Blasts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were killed and
39 others injured in two blasts in the past 24 hours in Anantnag
and Poonch districts of India-held Jammu and Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said four people were killed and another
seriously wounded when an improvised explosive device exploded in
Poonch district Tuesday. In another blast, three people were
killed and 38 others wounded, 10 of them seriously, near a bus
stop in Anantnag district in south Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
Nobody has claimed responsibility for the blasts so far. The
incidents are being looked into by the police. 
</P>
