<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Slightly Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed slightly higher Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index was 2.1
points higher at 464.12, the all-share Emas Index added 0.64 of a
point to 122.44, the Industrial Index gained 0.03 of a point to
876.57 and the Second Board Index rose 0.29 of a point to 132.48.
</P>
<P>
Gainers beat losers by 328 to 316 while 156 counters were
unchanged, 121 counters untraded and 44 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased to 192.851 million shares valued
at 333.739 million ringgit (87.826 million U.S. dollars) from
Monday's 178.354 million shares amounting to 255.513 million
ringgit (67.24 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the main board rose to 168.541 million shares
valued at 280.13 million ringgit (73.718 million dollars) from
Monday's 153.176 million shares amounting to 200.258 million
ringgit (52.699 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Second board turnover was lower at 24.31 million shares worth
53.609 million ringgit (13.318 million dollars) from 25.178
million shares valued at 55.255 million ringgit (14.54 million
dollars) on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals were also lower at 4.542 million shares valued
at 12.426 million ringgit (3.27 million dollars) from Monday's
12.719 million shares worth 20.018 million ringgit (5.267 million
dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
