<HEADLINE> Singapore Stock Market Closes Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed lower on
the Singapore Stock Market Tuesday as players remained cautious
ahead of a meeting of the U.S. Federal Reserve's policy-making
committee later Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Traders said the overnight strength on Wall Street contributed
to a jump in the morning session.
</P>
<P>
However, the market was weighed down by rating agency Moody's
downgrade of Japan's debt ratings, they said.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) dipped by 5.98 points
to end at 1,235.76. The volume totaled 235.71 million units valued
at 373.86 million Singapore dollars (about 229.22 million U.S.
dollars). Losers edged out gainers by 212 to 68 with 138 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
DBS Land topped the actives chart of the day with a turnover of
24.22 million units. KepLand was the second most heavily traded
stock with 14.69 million shares done. Wing T was next with 12.74
million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH 100 led the gainers of the day as it gained 30 cents to
close at 15.4 Singapore dollars. DBS edged up 20 cents to finish
at 6.35 Singapore dollars. Boustd S inched up 18 cents to end at
1.28 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 led the descent of the day with a
loss of 70 cents to finish at 22.8 Singapore dollars. Seaview
retreated 30 cents to close at 4.1 Singapore dollars. YHS slid 12
cents to end at 3.08 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
