<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Turkish Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Turkish newspapers Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Radikal (Radical):
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail Cem said Monday that Turkey
will take measures, including economic sanctions, if necessary, to
press Italy to extradite Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) leader
Abdullah Ocalan to Ankara for trial.
</P>
<P>
The PKK leader was arrested by the Italian police last week
when he attempted to enter the country with a false passport.
</P>
<P>
Milliyet (National):
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish Intelligence authorities have confirmed that Ocalan
has a total of 1 billion U.S. dollars in Syria's banks.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the money is earned through drug
trafficking and other illegal means.
</P>
<P>
Sabah (Morning):
</P>
<P>
-- Describing Ocalan as "a brutal murderer," the U.S. has
called on Italian government to hand over the PKK leader to Turkey.
</P>
<P>
"Arrest of Ocalan is a very important step in struggle with
terrorism. We believe that this terrorist will be extradited and
will be tried before Justice," State Department spokesman James
Rubin said at a press conference Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
