<HEADLINE> Xiong Guangkai Meets Slovakian Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief
of the People's Liberation Army (PLA) General Staff, met today
with a delegation of Slovakian military officers led by Milan
Stranaza.
</P>
<P>
Stranaza is the director of the Department for Defense
Policy and Army Development under the Slovakian Defense Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Xiong briefed the delegation on China's defense
policy, as well as the national construction and military
modernization.
</P>
<P>
He voiced satisfaction for the continuing development of
bilateral relations and military ties between the two countries,
and expressed the hope that the two armies will expand exchanges
in order strengthen friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Stranaza praised China's achievements in the reform and opening
drive, and pledged to continue to promote the growth of ties
between the two armies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
