<BODY>
<HEADLINE> APEC Leaders Hold Dialogue With Business Representatives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 17 (Xinhua)-- Leaders of the APEC member
economies held a dialogue here Tuesday afternoon with
representatives from the world business community in an effort to
find solutions to the current financial chaos.
</P>
<P>
The dialogue, convened by Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohamad, is being attended by 63 representatives of the Business
Advisory Council of the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC).
</P>
<P>
In his opening remarks, Mahathir said that the APEC meeting
this year is held in an environment when most of the member
economies have been hit by financial chaos and are striving to
recover their vitality.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said that the most urgent task for now is to "restore
the investors' confidence" and to urge member economies to
contribute to rebuilding the world and regional economy.
</P>
<P>
The dialogue, which comprises two sessions, is expected to last
about an hour.
</P>
<P>
During the first session, the business representatives focused
their questions or remarks mainly on ways to help the member
economies and international corporations walk out of the shadow of
the crisis.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
