<HEADLINE> Environmental-Friendly Heating Opens in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, November 17 (Xinhua) -- China's first environmentally-
friendly heating recently entered operation in the Tanggu
District in Tianjin, a port city some 100 km east of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The 85-mw plant, which can provide heating for one million
square meters, features advanced equipment which reduces coal
consumption from 38 kg to 23 kg per sq.m., power consumption by 50
percent, and dust emissions by more than 65 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
