<HEADLINE> China Increases Winter Crop Coverage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, November 17 (Xinhua) -- China has planted winter crops
on 46.6 million ha this year, one million ha more than last year's
figure.
</P>
<P>
Grain crops accounted for 30.5 million ha, up 266,600 ha, with
rapeseed planted on 6.13 million ha, or roughly same as last
year's area.
</P>
<P>
Farmers throughout the country planted winter wheat on 23
million ha, or 90 percent of the targeted coverage.
</P>
<P>
Eight leading wheat growing areas, including Henan, Hebei and
Shandong provinces, introduced hybrid wheat strains to 1.5 million
ha, up some 533,300 ha.
</P>
<P>
Machinery was used to plant crops on 16 million ha, up by one
million ha on 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
