<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0830 GMT, November 17 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- The European Union (EU) has submitted its pilot
projects to help special groups of people use "easy euro" at the
time of transition to the euro, the European Commission said here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Commission said that for the first time they proposed the
projects for evaluating specific difficulties which may arise for
three target groups: the elderly, the socio-economically
disadvantaged, as well as the blind and persons with impaired
vision. (EU-Euro)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ROME -- European countries should create a defense agency of
their own within the framework of the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO), Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini said
here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Dini made the call at the opening ceremony of a two-day Western
European Union (WEU) foreign and defense ministers meeting, at
which the representatives from 18 WEU countries will discuss
defense cooperation in Europe. He said that European countries
should establish a European defense and security pillar within the
NATO framework, which will enjoy independent decision-making
powers. (EU-Defense)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR -- Malaysian Works Minister S. Samy Vellu Tuesday
asked U.S. Vice President Al Gore to retract his statement
supporting the anti-government "reformation movement" in Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Gore said at a dinner Monday night for over 1,000 government
officials and captains of industry from the Pacific Rim that the
people who had been involved in the "reformation Movement" were
the "brave people of Malaysia." Describing Gore's remarks as a
"blantant interference in Malaysia's internal affairs, Samy Vellu
said that Gore's remarks had irked many Malaysians.
(Malaysia-US-Gore)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR -- The United States and Japan launched a joint
initiative here Monday night to help Asian nations affected by the
economic crisis obtain financing to revive their banking systems
and remove obstacles to restructuring.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time since the crisis which began in July
1997 that the United States has come forward to help the troubled
economies. U.S. Vice President Al Gore, who is here representing
President Bill Clinton to attend the 6th APEC Leaders Meeting,
said the initiative, known as the Asian Growth and Recovery
Program (AGRP), would be implemented with the help of Asian
Development Bank and World Bank. (US-Japan-Asia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
COLOMBO -- A priceless Sri Lankan artifact, the Thara Devi
bronze statue dating back to the 5th century BC, has been stolen
from the Anuradhapura Archaeological Museum in North Central
Province, according to reports reaching here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Although the security guards who were on duty have been
arrested by the police, no further headway has been made. The
missing statue was kept in a glass case with similar other
statues. The statue was found missing by a guard last Friday
morning. (Sri Lanka-Stolen Statue) 
</P>
</TEXT>
