<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Israeli Soldiers Killed in Southern Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Three Israeli soldiers were
killed and four others wounded Monday by a powerful roadside bomb
in southern Lebanon, Israel Radio reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The bomb went off some 30 meters from an Israeli military
outpost in the Israeli-occupied security zone when the soldiers
were on their way to a military drill, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, has claimed
responsibility for the attack.
</P>
<P>
The bomb attack came hours after Israeli warplanes raided
Hezbollah bases in southern Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah said in a statement that the deadly bombing attack
was in response to the continuing Israeli air raids, the radio
said.
</P>
<P>
The latest fatalities have brought the number to 18 of Israeli
soliders killed this year in southern Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The self-declared security zone was set up by Israel in 1985
with the claimed aim of shielding its north from Lebanese
guerrillas' cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah has been spearheading a guerrilla war to try to drive
the Israeli occupation troops out of southern Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The 1,200-square-meter zone is a flashpoint of frequent
roadside bomb attacks, rocket raids and fierce ground clashes.
</P>
<P>
In April, Israeli inner cabinet approved the U.N. resolution
425 and offered to withdraw its troops from southern Lebanon
provided Lebanese government agrees to guarantee the security of
northern Israel by curbing cross-border guerrilla attacks.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon, Syria which has great influence on Lebanon, have
rejected the offer and demanded an unconditional Israeli pullout
in light with the resolution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
