<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania's Food Industry Continues Shrinking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Romanian food processing
industry has been shrinking since the beginning of the 1990s, with
the current outputs of main products being less than half of those
eight years ago.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the Ministry of Agriculture and Food
Industries indicated that dairy production this year is expected
to plummet by 61 percent to 220 million liters from 560 million in
1990.
</P>
<P>
Domestic animal slaughtering is likely to drop 60 percent to
380,000 tons from 947,000 tons, while pastry production will fall
75 percent to 77,000 tons from 306,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, wine and beer outputs will go down by 33 percent and 13
percent respectively to 550 million and 910 million liters.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attributed the continuous shrinking to large numbers
of corporate bankruptcies arising from economic
restructuring. Imported foreign goods have also squeezed the
uncompetitive local industries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
