<HEADLINE> Young Chinese Girl Regains Speech </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Xie Qiongjie, a young girl
in central China's Hunan Province, has regained her ability to
speak following six oral cavity operations.
</P>
<P>
Thirteen years ago, Xie, 17, contracted middle ear infections
in both ears, but recovered from the disease following a series of
penicillin injections.
</P>
<P>
Nonetheless, she gradually found it increasingly difficult in
opening her mouth and could only consume a liquid diet through a
small opening in her teeth.
</P>
<P>
Xie suffered from facial deformation, and she totally lost the
ability to speak a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Plastic surgeons at the No.2 Hospital at the Hunan Medical
University recently completed six surgical procedures to reshape
and repair Xie's lower jaw and irregular teeth.
</P>
<P>
Xie regained her ability to speak in nine days and is
expected to be able to eat normally in about eight weeks.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
