<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hongkong Bank to Start Services in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Hongkong Bank plans to start
factoring and forfeiting services in India to help traders hedge
risks and finance the growing business, The Observer of Business
and Politics said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"Hongkong Bank will start factoring and forfeiting services
early next year from Mumbai and will shortly extend them to other
parts of the country," the paper quoted Kersi Patel, local head of
the bank trade services as saying.
</P>
<P>
These services would help businesses operate without problems
of delayed payments, adequacy of cash flow, debt collection and
bad debts. Factoring helps in financing and collecting of account
receivable, provides finance for the seller by way of advance
payments and protect against default in payment by buyer.
</P>
<P>
Forfeiting is the discounting of export receivable due at a
future date by a forfeiter, mostly a bank, from an exporter on a
without recourse basis. It is used for specific export-related
transactions of medium to long-term maturity.
</P>
<P>
Hongkong Bank is the first to offer export factoring services
in India and has already received Reserve Bank of India permission
for the service, Kersi Patel said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981117.0201 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-17 </DATE_TIME>
