<HEADLINE> Experts Predict Birth Peak in 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Experts predict that the year
2000 might possibly witness a peak in child births since an
increasing number of young couples hope to have their child
precisely at the turn of the century, according to today's Beijing
Morning Post.
</P>
<P>
The World Health Organization (WHO) recently announced that any
child born at 0:00 on January 1, 2000, will be a "Century Baby"
and as such will enjoy a series of "world-class" preferential
perks.
</P>
<P>
The gestation period to ensure the possibility of having a
"Century Baby" should fall between late March and early
April 1999.
</P>
<P>
Qu Chuanyan, a professor at the Women's and Children's
Healthcare Center at the No.1 Hospital under Beijing Medical
Sciences University, does not agree with the choice of many young
couples.
</P>
<P>
Qu, an expert on healthy births, said that having a "Century
Baby" does not necessarily ensure a healthy baby.
</P>
<P>
Qu pointed out giving birth to a child is a natural thing and
no artificial factors should be used to intervene. 
</P>
</TEXT>
