<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanxi Approves Afforestation Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, November 17 (Xinhua) -- North China's Shanxi Province
plans to develop a 1,046-km shelterbelt system along four national
highway trunk lines between now and next Spring.
</P>
<P>
The plan calls for the province to carry out afforestation
programs over 9,500 hectares of barren hills, plant trees to form
5,400 hectares of economic forests and afforest 436 villages.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi is located on the Loess Plateau and suffers from heavy
soil erosion resulting from a low forest coverage rate.
</P>
<P>
The afforestation program is part of a strategy for sustained
development designed to provide both economic and social benefits,
according to a provincial official.  
</P>
