<HEADLINE> Philippines to Facilitate Legal Services to Poor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Manila, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The labor authorities and the
Public Attorney's Office (PAO) of the Philippines have forged an
agreement to facilitate legal service to the public, especially
poor workers, the Philippines News Agency said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The joint effort of the National Labor Relations
Commission-Public Assistance Center (NLRC-PAC) and the PAO aims to
carry out the government's agenda of delivering direct and fast
services to the poor, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Records at the NLRC-PAC showed that indigent workers often
asked for the assistance of legal counsel to pursue their cases.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the NLRC may refer or endorse to the PAO
all persons seeking assistance involving legal matters, the news
agency said.
</P>
<P>
The NLRC would provide office space for the representative of
the PAO in its main office to make the PAO accessible to the
public seeking legal assistance.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, the chief public attorney concerned would
assign the case or problem to the proper district public attorney
for immediate action. 
</P>
</TEXT>
