<HEADLINE> Southeastern Chinese Province Encouraging Mountain Area Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, November 17 (Xinhua) -- China's Fujian Province has
developed policies recently to stimulate the economy in
mountainous areas.
</P>
<P>
A provincial government official says that Fujian will allocate
funds for infrastructure, improve the investment environment,
develop education and science and technology, and support pillar
industries in mountainous areas.
</P>
<P>
Mountains and hilly areas cover over 80 percent of Fujian and
economic development in these areas has lagged far behind that of
coastal parts of the province.
</P>
<P>
With the help of these policies, by the year 2000, the GDP in
these parts of Fujian is expected to be over eight times that of
1980. 
</P>
