<HEADLINE> Chinese Publication of Ancient Tablet Inscriptions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, November 17 (Xinhua) -- China has published a
100-volume set of rubbings of inscriptions on ancient stone
tablets.
</P>
<P>
It has nine parts corresponding to historical periods from the
Warring States (475-221 B.C.) to the Republic of China (1912-1949)
and contains 20,000 kinds of rubbings of inscriptions on stone
tablets, sculptures, carved paintings, Buddhist scriptures, and
epitaphs.
</P>
<P>
The inscriptions deal with history, geology, politics, the
economy, military affairs, religion, literature, art, technology,
architecture and folk customs.
</P>
<P>
The book was published by the Zhongzhou Ancient Book Publishing
House in Henan Province. The items were selected from 100,000
pieces of rubbing items stored in the Beijing Library. 
</P>
</TEXT>
