<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hebei Province Witnesses Declining Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, November 17 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province recorded an import-export volume of 2.88 billion US
dollars for the first three quarters of the year, a 1.2-percent
drop on the 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
Experts attributed the decrease mainly to the financial
crisis sweeping Asia.
</P>
<P>
Exports fell 1.6 percent to 2.26 billion US dollars, while
imports edged up by 0.5 percent to 621 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Some 58.6 percent of the exports in the period went to Asia,
down 68.4 percent on the previous year's period.
</P>
<P>
Exports to Latin America grew by 59 percent, with exports to
Europe growing by 31.7 percent and to North America by 23 percent.
</P>
<P>
The slow growth in foreign trade and rapidly changing markets
are expected to help accelerate efforts to optimize the local
export mix.
</P>
<P>
The province exported primary goods valued at 636 million US
dollars during the period, down 26 percent on the 1997
figure. However, exports of manufactured goods, machinery and
electronic products grew by 14 percent to 1.91 billion US
dollars. 
</P>
