<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Company Uses Deodorized Fenugreek in Diabetes Treatment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, November 16 (Xinhua) -- A fat-free and deodorized
form of fenugreek, a traditional medicinal plant for diabetes
treatment, will dispel patients' worry about it pungent taste, a
U.S. pharmaceutical company said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Nutricept Inc., based in Dallas, said that its alternative
medicine with fenugreek, named Limitrol-DM, will help diabetes
patients maintain blood glucose control as an adjunct to diet or
prescription medication.
</P>
<P>
Nutricept said that studies in past decades had confirmed
fenugreek's blood glucose lowering effect. Recent studies deemed
the essential to preventing diabetes complications. Fenugreek, an
extremely potent fiber, has also been shown to lower cholesterol
and promote weight loss.
</P>
<P>
Fenugreek is an annual plant indigenous to North Africa and
widely cultivated in India. In the United States, fenugreek is on
the list of foods and spices generally recognized as safe.
</P>
<P>
However, in its raw form, fenugreek's taste and smell are
prohibitively pungent for the average Westerner, which has limited
its popularity, said Nutricept. The company has developed a form
that eliminates the offensive taste and odor.
</P>
<P>
According to the company, the medical food helps diabetes
patients control their blood glucose levels by diminishing the
rise in after-meal blood sugar by 40 percent. In pudding form, it
was clinically shown to reduce serum total cholesterol by 20
percent in just six weeks.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the new diabetes remedy, the Journal of the
American Medical Association in its latest issue stresses that
emphasis must be placed on the need for convincing data on safety
and therapeutic efficacy. Nutricept said it has been addressing
these key issues through its product research.
</P>
<P>
According to the American Diabetes Association, diabetes is a
serious disease affecting more than 16 million people in the
United States alone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981117.0233 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-17 </DATE_TIME>
