<HEADLINE> Tianjin Makes Headway in Old City Reconstruction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, November 17 (Xinhua) -- A new residential and
commercial center has emerged in the old section of Tianjin
following a three year construction effort.
</P>
<P>
The Xin'an Shopping Center, one of the three major projects in
the reconstruction program known as the Dragon Town of Tianjin,
opened last year, and the Xin'an Garden project was recently
completed.
</P>
<P>
The effort to relocate residents is nearing completion and
construction of a new residential complex will begin by the end
this year.
</P>
<P>
The new urban center will cover 1.5 sq.km., some 40 percent of
which will feature landscaped areas. Buildings ranging from eight
to 22 floors will ring the section, and the project will be
completed over a 15 year period.
</P>
<P>
The reconstruction project has attracted a number of investors,
including the Anderson Group and the New World Group from Hong
Kong, as well as COSCO (China Ocean Shipping Corporation).
</P>
<P>
The old area was built in 1404 and was formerly the central
political, economic and cultural district in Tianjin. The
developers also plan to build a drum tower in the central square
and refurbish a number of historical sites.  
</P>
</TEXT>
