<HEADLINE> Jiang: Developed Countries Responsible for Handling Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin said here Tuesday that to deal with financial crisis needs
global cooperation, and developed countries have irreplaceable
responsibility for that.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark while meeting with Singapore's Prime
Minister Goh Chok Tong. "The financial crisis starting from
Southeast Asian countries last year has so far affected the whole
world. It has brought about severe challenges especially to the
developing countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Consequences of the crisis is far more serious than expected.
Presently, it seems that it will take longer time for Southeast
and East Asian countries to walk out of the shadow of the
financial crisis," Jiang added.
</P>
<P>
According to the Chinese President, the financial crisis has
also affected China greatly and brought about some difficulties
for the country's exports.
</P>
<P>
But China will take up its duties and responsibilities and
stick to its promise of keeping the value of the Chinese yuan,
Jiang reaffirmed.
</P>
<P>
"China will reach this year's goal of economic development
through expanding internal needs, and keep on the reforms
including the reform of the financial system," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Goh Chok Tong praised China's policy of keeping the value of
the Chinese yuan, holding that it's a big help to countries
severely affected by the financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
He proposed that the APEC Leaders Meeting have in-depth
discussions on taking effective measures and getting rid of the
crisis.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China attaches importance the relationship of
friendly cooperation with Singapore and its positive function in
international and regional affairs.
</P>
<P>
Expressing gratitude to Goh Chok Tong for the aids the
Singaporean government and people have given to the flood-stricken
areas of China, Jiang said that China is willing to join hands
with Singapore to boost the cooperation of mutual benefit in all
fields. 
</P>
