<HEADLINE> Jiang: Chinese Indonesians Should Enjoy Equal Treatment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin said here Tuesday that Chinese Indonesians, after acquiring
the nationality of the Indonesia, have become members of the
country and they should enjoy equal treatment and rights as
ordinary Indonesians.
</P>
<P>
China doesn't have any "private interests" in the matters of
overseas Chinese and people with Chinese origin, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark while meeting with President of Indonesia
Jusuf Habibie. Jiang believed that the President and Indonesian
government will understand the feelings and concerns of the
Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
"We hold that proper solution of the issue of Chinese
Indonesians will not only serve to the long-term stability of
Indonesia, but also to the smooth development of the relationship
of friendly cooperation between us two big neighboring countries,"
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Habibie said that Chinese Indonesians are all Indonesians, and
a member of the big multi-nationality family of the Indonesians.
</P>
<P>
Indonesian government holds that the event which happened in
May was a kind of crime and that it doesn't tolerate this kind of
things to happen again.
</P>
<P>
He promised that Indonesia will deal with the event according
to law seriously.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral relations, Jiang said Indonesia is a friendly and
close neighbor of China. To further develop the bilateral
relationship is a set policy of China.
</P>
<P>
"Although the domestic situation of Indonesia has witnessed
drastic changes this year, the determination of the Chinese
government to consolidate and boost the bilateral relationship of
good neighborly and friendly cooperation doesn't change," Jiang
noted.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said there doesn't exist fundamental conflict between
China and Indonesia, and that the economic construction of the
respective countries and the safeguarding of prosperity and
stability of the region are our common goals. 
</P>
