<HEADLINE> Beijing Opens Mental Health Rehabilitation Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Farming activities such as
growing vegetables and raising pigs have been used to rehabilitate
Chinese mental patients, according to today's Beijing Morning Post.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's Chaoyang District is currently constructing a farming
rehabilitation center which stresses psychological counselling
needed to rehabilitate mental patients.
</P>
<P>
Beijing reportedly has a 340,000 mental patients. However, the
city has less than a dozen mental hospitals with merely 8,000
beds. The lack of beds has seriously hampered the rehabilitation
capabilities of mental health centers.
</P>
<P>
The Chaoyang rehabilitation center will not only feature a
clinic, medical facility and physical fitness center, but will
also offer more agricultural activities related to fish ponds,
greenhouses and vegetable gardens.
</P>
<P>
Mental patients will work on voluntary basis with income based
on work contributed.
</P>
<P>
Medical experts note the good environment will promote
rehabilitation efforts.
</P>
<P>
The center's fees are only a third of normal charges at regular
hospitals.  
</P>
</TEXT>
