<HEADLINE> "Time Bank" for Elderly in Northern China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Northern China's Shanxi
Province has set up a "time bank" for the elderly in the capital
city, Taiyuan.
</P>
<P>
Any elderly person can become a member of the "bank" by just
filling in a form, and the "bank" will then ask them to offer free
help to other old people when they have spare time and they
themselves can get help from others at any time.
</P>
<P>
According Miss Xu, who is in charge of the project, the "time
bank" is set up by the Taiyuan Telecommunications Bureau and a
local advertising company to help the elderly make better use of
their spare time.
</P>
<P>
She said that the number of old people is growing, as is the
proportion of the elderly among the population as a whole. This
kind of project can better help the elderly because many young
people are busy with their work and don't have time to take care
of the elderly.
</P>
<P>
The project is also developed so that people above the age of
85 who do not have children can get care.
</P>
<P>
This kind of organization first appeared in Japan, which has an
aging society.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
