<HEADLINE> Hebei Province Increases Cotton Purchases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province, a leading
cotton producer in north China, has purchased 88,000 tons of
ginned cotton, up 50,000 tons on last year's figure.
</P>
<P>
The province's favorable climate and increased acreage sown to
insect-resistant cotton yielded a good harvest for the year, with
projections calling for the total output to hit 250,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The provincial agricultural development bank has granted 700
million yuan in loans for cotton purchases. Industrial,
commercial, public security, pricing and marketing departments
have also supervised management of cotton market in order to curb
illegal practices such as IOUs.
</P>
<P>
Individuals and institutions are prohibited from purchasing,
processing and ginning cotton. 
</P>
