<HEADLINE> Cuban Cigars Sell Well on Foreign Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Cuba's Partagas brand cigars
are currently sold in 60 countries, earning the country more than
2.3 million U.S. dollars so far this year, the state-run company's
manager Mario Exposito said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The cigars are bought by Italians, French, Canadians, Spanish
smokers and even by people in the United States breaking the
U.S. embargo against Cuba, the manager said.
</P>
<P>
Cuba produced a total of 100 million cigars for export last
year and earned about 180 million dollars. It expects to produce
160 million cigars this year and 175 million in 1999. The figure
could soar to 200 million in 2000. 
</P>
