<HEADLINE> U.N. Official Calls for Albanians' Turnout in Referendum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Visiting U.N.
Under-Secretary-General Vladimir Petrovsky Monday called on the
Albanians to take part in the November 22 referendum on the
constitution.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a national conference on human rights held in
Tirana, Prtrovski said he hopes all Albanian citizens will turn
out in the forthcoming referendum as the constitution is the basic
law ensuring human rights of the international standards.
</P>
<P>
The constitution to be voted on was drafted earlier this year
and is expected to fill up the vacancy following the annulment in
1990 of the former basic law.
</P>
<P>
The new constitution prescribes that Albania shall be a
democracy with a market economy, which guarantees private
property, human rights and the separation of the legislative,
executive and judicial powers.
</P>
<P>
But the opposition Democratic Party has urged boycott of the
vote, saying that it would not recognize the outcome of the
referendum.
</P>
<P>
While meeting with Albanian President Rexhep Meidani on Monday,
Prtrovski said the international conference held on October 30 in
Tirana showed that the international community was much concerned
with Albania.
</P>
<P>
The visiting U.N. official believed that the Albanian people
would be able to demonstrate their political maturity through
their own judgement. 
</P>
