<HEADLINE> Nicaragua Reports Loss in Banana Exports After Hurricane </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Nicaragua has lost 90,000
U.S. dollars in its banana export earnings in the aftermath of
Hurricane Mitch, press reports said Monday.
</P>
<P>
About 170,000 crates of bananas due to be exported have been
held up in the border town of El Guasaule in the past three weeks
because of the hurricane, the Nicaraguan banana producers'
association said.
</P>
<P>
Nicaragua traditionally exported its bananas to Europe and the
United States through the ports of Puerto Castilla and Puerto
Cores of Honduras, the worst hit by Mitch in its ravage of Central
America.
</P>
<P>
Mitch also devastated 850 hectares, or 35 percent, of banana
plantations in Nicaragua. 
</P>
</TEXT>
