<HEADLINE> French President Begins Visit to Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, November 16 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques
Chirac on Monday started a visit to Nicaragua, which was hit by
Hurricane Mitch in the last week of October.
</P>
<P>
Chirac is scheduled to travel to the Tipitapa region, 30
kilometers from Nicaragua's capital, to inspect the devastation
wreaked by Mitch and offer his sympathy with the people in the
afflicted area.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, Chirac announced in Guatemala that France would
cancel the debts of Guatemala, Honduras, Nicaragua and El
Salvador, the worst affected by Hurricane Mitch.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Nicaragua's foreign debt totaled 65
million U.S. dollars. 
</P>
