<HEADLINE> Importing Peonies In Central Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUOYANG, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Luoyang, a central China city
known for peony growing, has imported about 1,000 peony stems of
56 rare varieties from Japan in a bid to boost its flower-related
business.
</P>
<P>
The city has a more than 1,000-year history of peony
growing. Local farmers now grow 502 varieties of peony on about
253 hectares of land, 166.7 hectares of which are for the open
market. Ten production bases specialize in growing peonies.
</P>
<P>
It exports peonies to 15 countries and regions and sells to
mainland areas, with annual profits from domestic sales exceeding
five million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Pony exports have been growing rapidly since growers started
selling peonies abroad via the Internet in August. It is expected
that this year's earnings from peony exports will be close to one
million yuan.  
</P>
