<P>
SHANGHAI, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Bernard Lacoste, the
president of France's Lacoste, said during a recent visit to
Shanghai, China's fashion center, that China will become its
largest overseas production base and sales center in the near
future.
</P>
<P>
Lacoste's products are too expensive for Chinese right now, but
China's market potential is unparalleled, he said.
</P>
<P>
The first store in China to sell Lacoste clothing opened in
Shanghai in 1995, and today there are more than 50 stores in 24
major Chinese cities specializing in Lacoste products. The
alligator can also be found in big department stores.
</P>
<P>
Lacoste's sales China over the last four years grew 50 percent
annually and Bernard Lacoste predicted that it won't take long for
China to become Lacoste's biggest market in Asia or possibly in
the world.
</P>
<P>
He also spoke highly of China's progress in clothing
production, saying that the quality of loosely woven shirts made
here is up to French standards.
</P>
<P>
