Camdessus said that Latin America's reaction proved that the
region's economies were "out of the crisis."
</P>
<P>
He noted that an IMF rescue package for Brazil "gives an idea
of the magnitude of the support the international community is
ready to give to voluntary and healthy policies to resist the
crisis."
</P>
<P>
He said Latin American economies would benefit from the support
package given to Brazil in exchange for a strict austerity
policy. 
