for DJK Wurzburg in Germany, Radoslav Nestrovic, picked 17th by
Minnesota, is playing for Kinder Bologna in Italy, and Vladimir
Stepania, chosen 27th by Seattle, is playing for Olympia Ljubjana
of Slovenia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981117.0303 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nottingham Forest Draw Derby County in Premier League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Dutch international, who came back to the Midlands club
two weeks ago after refusing to play in the opening months of the
season, put Forest 2-1 up when he headed home Scott Gemmill's
corner in the 62nd minute.
</P>
<P>
But Forest's hopes of a first league win since August lasted
just 10 minutes, Argentine defender Horacio Carbonari scoring his
first goal for Derby to make it 2-2.
</P>
<P>
After a disappointing first half Derby had gone ahead in the
56th minute when Thierry Bonalair tripped Dean Sturridge in the
box and Tony Dorigo calmly stroked in the penalty.
</P>
<P>
The lead lasted only two minutes, Dougie Freedman tucking away
the rebound after Derby goalkeeper Russell Hoult had blocked his
initial shot.
</P>
<P>
Then came Van Hooijdonk's goal, which the Dutchman celebrated
virtually alone as most of his disgruntled team mates showed what
they thought of his self-imposed exile by refusing to
congratulate him.
</P>
<P>
Hoult was taken to hospital later for precautionary X-rays
after being knocked unconscious in a collision.
</P>
<P>
The point lifted Forest one place, up to third-last in the
standings. Derby remain eighth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
