<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China-Made Planes Enjoy Unblemished Flight Safety Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The 123 aircraft of the Yun-7
family manufactured by China's Xi'an Aircraft Corporation had a
flight safety record of over 600,000 hours by October 28 this
year, a company spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft series has reached advanced international safety
and reliability standards, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
There are 69 Yun-7 aircraft currently in service. Since the
first plane was delivered to a Chinese airline in 1984, the Yun-7
series have become the major aircraft used in the country's civil
aviation sector.
</P>
<P>
Yun-7 planes are also configured for cargo, flight instruction,
scientific research and business purposes.
</P>
<P>
The company has sold eight Yun-7 aircraft to foreign
companies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
