<HEADLINE> Marco Fu Makes Mark on and off Table </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He forged a 5-3 overnight lead over Gary Wilkinson who becomes
one of Fu's new stable-mates after the 20-year-old from Hong Kong
became the latest signing of top manager Ian Doyle.
</P>
<P>
Last month's Grand Prix finalist requires four of Tuesday's
remaining nine frames to book his place in the last 32 of the 46
0,000 pounds (about 764,000 U.S. dollars) tournament.
</P>
<P>
That represents a useful display by Fu, who despite his fine
performance at Preston, can't match most of his opponents for
experience.
</P>
<P>
Wilkinson, the former World Matchplay champion, is one of the
most tactically-aware players in the game but he couldn't hold on
to a 3-1 interval advantage against the youngster from Happy
Valley.
</P>
<P>
Fu reeled off four frames without reply with two breaks of 83
to transform the contest.
</P>
<P>
His capture by Scottish businessman Doyle means he becomes the
20th member of the formidable Cuemasters stable including former
world champions Stephen Hendry and Ken Doherty plus current UK
Champion Ronnie O'Sullivan. 
</P>
