<HEADLINE> Duma Not to Ratify Start-2 Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 16 (Xinhua) -- The Russian State Duma, or the
lower house of parliament, can hardly ratify the Start-2 treaty,
for many factions are to vote against the ratification, the
Itar-Tass news agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Itar-Tass, Vladimir Volkov, a member of
the Duma defense committee, said that in the run-up to hearings on
Start-2 due in late November, many factions in Duma showed
opposition to the treaty's ratification.
</P>
<P>
Volkov said, "I guess no qualified majority will be gained in a
vote for ratification of this document. Many large factions are
not ready to vote `for,' presuming that the treaty in its very
essence can damage interests of Russia's national security."
</P>
<P>
He noted that a major number of Duma members are uncertain
about Russia's being on schedule with equipping its army with the
new missile system Topol-M as planned.
</P>
<P>
Former Russian Defense Minister Igor Rodionov said at the State
Duma Monday that Russia should not ratify the START-2 treaty.
</P>
<P>
Calling the treaty "a treacherous treaty," Rodionov said, "The
treaty was strategically disarming us."
</P>
<P>
He said, "Russia should withdraw from the treaty until it was
not too late."
</P>
<P>
In his opinion, under the critical situation in the economy of
the country, Russia is unable to keep pace with the USA in the
weapon's quantity and quality.
</P>
<P>
"Further deterioration of the economic situation and
destructive processes underway in the army will undermine our
combat efficiency without any ratification," Rodionov said.
</P>
<P>
He said Russia should proceed from its national interests when
considering the ratification problem, and should not "cater for
NATO and the USA."
</P>
<P>
The START-2 treaty signed by the United States and Russia in
1993 was ratified by the U.S. House of Representatives in January
1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
