<HEADLINE> Iran committed to tension defusing, Khatami says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami on Monday reiterated that defusing tension worldwide
is Iran's number one priority in its foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
While meeting with visiting Finnish Foreign Minister Tarja
Halonen here, Khatami said the world has suffered a lot from
terrorism in the 20th century, adding Iran is a victim of
terrorism.
</P>
